The paper discusses the development of a semantic enrichment process for mathematical formulae using generic LaTeX sources. This process involves inferring semantic information from the LaTeX sources and using it to build formula home pages. This work is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and computer vision (cs.CV).
